beer_description: St. Amand is a classic of the traditional Biere de Garde style. St. Amand contains only artesian well water, barley malt from the Champagne region and hops from Alsace. A dynamite beer with steak and chops and bistro fare in general.

A style of ale that was fashioned to survive the long voyage from England to India during the British colonization. Hops, hops, and more hops! Red Racer IPA has an intense aroma and a long lingering finish. A beer for the connoisseur, this is the Brewmaster's choice.

Malts: UK Maris Otter, Superior Pale
Ale Malt, Carastan Crystal Malt

Hops: German Magnum, 

Centennial, Amarillo, Simcoe

Colour/Clarity: Amber to Orange, Bright

Available In: Draught, Cans (355 and 473 ml), Bottle (650 ml)

SRM: 14

Red Racer Stout is deep, dark, smooth, and creamy. The use of oatmeal in the mashtun adds silkiness to the texture and body of this ale.

Malts: UK Maris Otter, Superior Pale Ale Malt, Blend of Crystal Malts, Roast Barley, Chocolate Malt

Hops: German Perle Hops
Colour/Clarity: Black

Available In: Draught, Bottles (650 ml)

SRM: 53
Combining their Old Sullivan Porter with Harvest Lager.
Made with Canadian Prairie two-row malted barley and hops imported from Germany and the Czech Republic. Red Truck Lager is a beer with world-class credential.

A blend of premium Belgian malts, plus German and Pacific Northwest hop varieties gives this luscious, copper-hued ale a wonderful complex aroma, a rich depth of flavour, and smooth drinkability. 5.1% Alcohol.
A classic American style pale ale with the distinctive pine and citrus character of its signature Cascade hops.
Golden European style pilsner with a Czech Saaz hop.

Our proud original. BC?s supreme craft cream ale. A smooth, dark, full bodied beer made with premium Canadian barley, specialty malts from the US and aroma hops from Washington State. Cold conditioned for over three weeks, this beer is easy drinking with a creamy smooth finish.
This beer has been fermented at cold temperatures and given a long maturation period. The result is a clean, refreshing, easy-drinking Session style Lager.
A rich golden color, this beer is made with Canadian barley and specialty malts from Scotland. Aroma hops from the Yakima Valley, provide a well-balanced bitterness and a slight citrus character.

R&B?s Red Devil Pale Ale is an English-style pale ale with a coppery red hue. Not to be confused with typical red and amber ales, Red Devil is crafted with the palate and bouquet in mind. A mix of 2-Row and C-75 malts are accentuated by the addition of Crystal, Fuggles, and Whitbread Goldings hops at three different stages in the brewing process. In keeping with English tradition, this little devil has a hoppy floral aroma and malty sweetness, which are followed by a slightly dry and very refreshing finish.

Beacon ESB is a copper coloured, medium bodied, generously hopped India Pale Ale.  Beacon possesses just the perfect balance of sharp hop flavour without being overly bitter.  The crisp, inviting aroma and unique, spicy taste will leave the palate yearning for more.

A blend of premium Belgian malts, plus German and Pacific Northwest hop varieties gives this luscious, copper-hued ale a wonderful complex aroma, a rich depth of flavour, and smooth drinkability. 5.1% Alcohol.
This real North Country brown ale is all about malt flavours using hops only as a balance to the smooth roast nut character.

A blend of premium Belgian malts, plus German and Pacific Northwest hop varieties gives this luscious, copper-hued ale a wonderful complex aroma, a rich depth of flavour, and smooth drinkability. 5.1% Alcohol.
Made with Canadian Prairie two-row malted barley and hops imported from Germany and the Czech Republic. Red Truck Lager is a beer with world-class credential.
Aromatic hops and firm malt backbone. India pale ale meets English bitters. Hopped with traditional English Kent Golding`s

BIG IS BEAUTIFUL!  The most fun loving, intelligent, attractive, lucky and prosperous Father of all Mission Springs Ales!  Coffee, chocolate and roasted flavours abound in this world class stout.

Style: Oatmeal Stout
Colour: 60 / Ibu: 21
4.5% alc./vol
We have RETIRED the Chief!!

The Kolsch style beer is nutty, spicy and very refreshing. Crystal and Munich malts are combined with European hops for a beer perfect for thirst quenching and pairing with spicy pastas or brick oven pizzas.

This classic wheat ale is cloudy, crisp and dry, with aromas of banana and clove ? great with brunch, patios, and bright dispositions. Let it shine.
Vaguely tart with light clove and banana flavours and aromas. Finishes crisp and dry.
Perfect pairing: Poached eggs or Weisswurst.

Brewed to the original recipe that put us on the map in '84, ISLAND LAGER combines premium ingredients to create one distinctly clean and refreshing hop taste.
Food Pairing: grilled foods like chicken and beef burgers.

The English know a thing or two about pale ale. West Coasters know a thing or two about having a good time. Naturally, we kept these facts in mind when we perfected the recipe for English Bay Pale Ale. Tradition is served in the smooth, mild flavour and caramel malt aroma, and that distinctive West Coast character comes through thanks to natural carbonation and careful maturing. The result? A real pale ale with will rise to any occasion.

Mild, bright and lightly hopped with a hint of Fraser Valley honey. It pairs up nicely with lighter seafoods and a thirst for adventure. Soft malt flavour with hints of honey, balanced with a light hop bitterness.
Perfect pairing: Grilled halibut or grilled spot prawns.
Hopluia utilizes a rare form of "dry hopping" in which hops are added directly to a secondary fermentation. The resulting aroma builds anticipation of a truly unique brew that heightens the senses.
Uva?eno speci?ln? pro Pivovarskou pivnici.

Bobby is light in color and full of flavor without being heavy. This is a traditional K?lsch-style ale, a type of beer that originated in the Cologne region of Germany prior to the development of lager yeast in the 1800's.

Heineken is a 5% ABV euro pale lager, made by Heineken International since 1873. It is available in a 4.3% alcohol by volume, in countries such as Ireland. It is the flagship product of the company and is made of purified water, malted barley, hops, and yeast. In 1886 H. Elion finished the development of the Heineken A-yeast. This is the yeast that is still used for the beer. The beer is force carbonated. It is popular in the United States, Europe and Middle Eastern countries.

beer_description: A Northern European-style lager, rich in flavor, with a crisp hop finish
A light, clean, crisp lager. Reminiscent of beers brewed in the early years of Seattle. Flavorful, yet light in alcohol.
Dark amber in color, Nightwatch is smooth and mellow with a subtle roast flavor and gentle hopping from Mt. Hood and Saaz hops. A true Northwestern original-style ale.
Light blond in color with a gentle malt flavor and subtle hop character. Islander is a blend of malted barley, wheat, and a combination of Yakima and Czech Republic hops.
A true English-style bitter that is rich in malt, hop flavor, and aroma. Brewed with no less than four types of malt, and English and Yakima hops.
Golden in color, light and refreshing with a citrus flavor, Clipper is bolder than most N.W. wheat beer. Made with malted wheat, pale barley malt and quality European hops.
The first beer brewed at Maritime Pacific. Red amber in color, malty, nut-like flavor derived from a blend of malted barley, wheat, and Yakima and European hops.

Brewed each year for the NCAA tournament, Slam Dunkel Weizenbock is a strong dark, unfiltered wheat beer. It is brewed with Northwest Klages/Harrington 2-row malt, Northwest winter wheat (25%), and Hugh Baird Crystal (70-80 L), Munich, Chocolate and Light Carastan malts. It is hopped with Centennial and Mt. Hood hops.
A Northwest interpretation of a Belgian tripel, Trombipulator was first brewed to commemorate Big Time's five hundredth brew. A very big and pale beer, and it is very heavily hopped.

A smooth, eminently drinkable stout on the order of Guinness draft, served on nitrogen to provide a solid and creamy head. The Buck is both stately and plump, a condition achieved through the combination of a partial sour mash, a deep roasted barley backbone, and the velvety texture of flaked barley.
A blend of dark malts and crystal malts gives our Porter a rich and smooth texture with a chocolaty finish. Hopped with Magnum, Liberty and Centennial.
Pale, Crystal and Munich with a touch of Chocolate malt for color. Malty sweetness starts this classic amber off with just enough hops to balance out the rich malt character
Brewed with Northwestern 2-row and a blend of Crystal malt. Light, crisp and citrusy to bring out that clean finish. Magnum, Cascade and Citra.
A pale, crisp, hoppy refresher. Lots of distinctive, spicy Cascade hops added in several stages during brewing, fermentation and conditioning.
Bigger and hoppy than Bhagwan?s. Brewed with a technique known as First Wort Hopping. Creating a bold hop flavor and a floral hop flavor with a touch of grapefruit in the finish.

The Immortal IPA :: Refreshing, hoppy, and strong.

A Northwest interpretation of a classic English style, golden copper in color and loaded with New World hop flavor and aroma. Brewed with Pale, Munich, Crystal and Cara-hell malts. Bittered with Chinook, finished with Amarillo and Centennial hops.

Note: The ABV for this beer varies between 4% ABV in Europe, 4.9% ABV in Australia, and 5% in the US.

First brewed by William and Ralph Foster in Melbourne in 1888.

With its Australian heritage, Foster's truly embodies the Australian ?no worries? attitude to life. It is an easy-drinking lager that is perfectly balanced with moderate vanilla tasting notes and no hard edges or bitter after taste for perfect refreshment.

Avatar Jasmine IPA :: A new incarnation of India Pale Ale. Brewed with Pale, 45? Crystal, Munich and Cara-hell malts. Bittered with German Northern Brewer and finished with Glacier and Amarillo hops. Dried jasmine flowers added in the boil and hopback. 6.3%  by volume.

Bifr?st Winter Ale :: Strong, hoppy and sm??th. Named for the mythical bridge connecting the mortal world to the heavens. Brewed with pale malt and small amounts of Munich and Crystal malts. Bittered with Magnum and finished with Chinook and Styrian Goldings hops. 7.6% ABV. 58 IBUs.
A touch more malt then a classic pilsner.  Bittered with German Northern Brewer and finished with Styrian Golding
